.TH HYPOT 3M 
.SH NAME
hypot \- Euclidean distance function
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B #include <math.h>
.PP
.B double hypot (x, y)
.br
.B double x, y;
.SH DESCRIPTION
.I Hypot\^
returns 
.PP
.RS
sqrt(x \(** x + y \(** y),
.RE
.PP
taking precautions against unwarranted overflows.
.SH DIAGNOSTICS
When the correct value would overflow,
.I hypot\^
returns
.SM
.B HUGE
and sets
.I errno\^
to
.SM
.B ERANGE.
.PP
These error-handling procedures may be changed with the function
.IR matherr (3M).
.SH SEE ALSO
matherr(3M), sqrt(3F).
